code: GF <- APOERES %>%   generate_oak_id_vars_adni(raw_src = "APOERES") %>%   mutate(     GFTESTCD = "APOE",     GFTEST = "Apolipoprotein E",     GFGRPID = COLPROT,     GFSTDTL = "GENOTYPE",     GFORRES = GENOTYPE,     GFSTRESC = str_replace_all(GENOTYPE, "(\\d+)", "ε\\1"),     GFDTC = create_iso8601(as.character(APTESTDT), .format = "y-m-d"),   ) %>%   derive_usubjid() %>%   assign_studyid_domain(domain = "GF") %>%   assign_visit_attr(check_missing_visnum = FALSE) %>%   derive_study_day_adni(     dm_domain = DM,     domain = "GF"   ) %>%   derive_seq(     tgt_var = "GFSEQ",     rec_vars = c("USUBJID", "GFTESTCD", "GFGRPID")   ) %>%   assign_vars_label(data_dict = gf_data_dic)

title: ADNIMERGE2-Derived-Data
text: VS dataset contains measurement finding blood pressure, heart beat, respiratory rate, temperature, weight height per visit per subject.
code: # Wide format VS <- VITALS %>%   mutate(VSDTC = create_iso8601(as.character(VISDATE), .format = "y-m-d")) %>%   select(     ORIGPROT, COLPROT, RID, VISCODE, VSDTC,     VSWEIGHT, VSWTUNIT, VSHEIGHT, VSHTUNIT, VSBPSYS, VSBPDIA, VSPULSE,     VSRESP, VSTEMP, VSTMPSRC, VSTMPUNT, VSHGTSC   ) %>%   generate_oak_id_vars_adni(raw_src = "VITALS") %>%   mutate(across(c(VSWEIGHT, VSHEIGHT, VSTEMP), ~ ifelse(.x == -1, NA, .x))) %>%   verify(all(VSWTUNIT %in% c("kilograms", "pounds") | is.na(VSWTUNIT))) %>%   verify(all(VSHTUNIT %in% c("centimeters", "inches") | is.na(VSHTUNIT))) %>%   verify(all(VSTMPUNT %in% c("Fahrenheit", "Celsius") | is.na(VSTMPUNT))) %>%   mutate(     VSWTUNIT_TRANSLATED = case_when(       VSWTUNIT %in% "kilograms" ~ "kg",       VSWTUNIT %in% "pounds" ~ "LB"     ),     VSHTUNIT_TRANSLATED = case_when(       VSHTUNIT %in% "centimeters" ~ "cm",       VSHTUNIT %in% "inches" ~ "inch"     ),     VSTMPUNT_TRANSLATED = case_when(       VSTMPUNT %in% "Fahrenheit" ~ "F",       VSTMPUNT %in% "Celsius" ~ "C"     ),   ) %>%   unite("WEIGHT", VSWEIGHT, VSWTUNIT_TRANSLATED, sep = "-") %>%   unite("HEIGHT", VSHEIGHT, VSHTUNIT_TRANSLATED, sep = "-") %>%   unite("TEMP", VSTEMP, VSTMPUNT_TRANSLATED, VSTMPSRC, sep = "-") %>%   mutate(     DIABP = ifelse(!is.na(VSBPDIA), paste0(VSBPDIA, "-", "mmHg"), NA),     SYSBP = ifelse(!is.na(VSBPSYS), paste0(VSBPSYS, "-", "mmHg"), NA),     PLUSE = ifelse(!is.na(VSPULSE), paste0(VSPULSE, "-", "beats/min"), NA),     RESP = ifelse(!is.na(VSRESP), paste0(VSRESP, "-", "breaths/min"), NA)   ) # Long format VS <- VS %>%   pivot_longer(     cols = c(WEIGHT, HEIGHT, TEMP, DIABP, SYSBP, PLUSE, RESP),     names_to = "VSTESTCD",     values_to = "VALUE"   ) %>%   set_dom_test(     .data_list = VS_TESTCD_LIST %>%       select(VSTESTCD, VSTEST),     merge_by = "VSTESTCD"   ) %>%   separate(VALUE, into = c("VSORRES", "VSORRESU", "VSLOC"), sep = "-") %>%   mutate(VSLOC = str_to_upper(VSLOC)) %>%   mutate(VSSTRESU = case_when(     VSORRESU %in% c("F", "C") ~ "C",     VSORRESU %in% c("cm", "inch") ~ "cm",     VSORRESU %in% c("kg", "LB") ~ "kg",     VSORRESU %in% c("mmHg", "beats/min", "breaths/min") ~ VSORRESU   )) %>%   # Unit conversion: conv_unit   mutate(     FROM_UNIT = case_when(       VSORRESU %in% "LB" ~ "lbs",       VSORRESU %in% c("C", "F", "cm", "inch", "kg") ~ VSORRESU,       TRUE ~ NA_character_     ),     TO_UNIT = case_when(       VSSTRESU %in% c("C", "kg", "cm") ~ VSSTRESU,       TRUE ~ NA_character_     )   ) %>%   rowwise() %>%   mutate(     VSSTRESN = ifelse(       VSTESTCD %in% c("WEIGHT", "HEIGHT", "TEMP") & !is.na(FROM_UNIT),       conv_unit(as.numeric(VSORRES), from = FROM_UNIT, to = TO_UNIT),       ifelse(VSTESTCD %in% c("DIABP", "SYSBP", "PLUSE", "RESP"),         as.numeric(VSORRES), NA_real_       )     )   ) %>%   mutate(     VSGRPID = COLPROT,     VSSTRESN = round(VSSTRESN, digits = 1),     VSSTRESC = as.character(VSSTRESN),     VSDRVFL = case_when(!is.na(FROM_UNIT) & FROM_UNIT != TO_UNIT ~ "Yes")   ) %>%   as_tibble() %>%   assert_non_missing(COLPROT, VISCODE, VSTEST) VS <- VS %>%   derive_usubjid() %>%   assign_studyid_domain(domain = "VS") %>%   assign_visit_attr() %>%   assign_epoch() %>%   derive_blfl_adni(     dm_domain = DM,     tgt_var = "VSBLFL"   ) %>%   derive_study_day_adni(     dm_domain = DM,     domain = "VS"   ) %>%   derive_seq(     tgt_var = "VSSEQ",     rec_vars = c("USUBJID", "VSTESTCD", "VSGRPID")   ) %>%   assign_vars_label(data_dict = vs_data_dic)

title: ADNIMERGE2-PACC-SCORE
text: article describes procedure calculate modified version Preclinical Alzheimer Cognitive Composite PACC score ADNI study based Donohue et al. (2014) approach. According Donohue et al. (2014), PACC score baseline standardize composite : Free Cued Selective Reminding Test (FCSRT) score Logical Memory IIa Delayed Recall (LM) score Digit Symbol Substitution Test (DSST) score, Mini-Mental State Examination (MMSE) total score component score required standardized corresponding baseline score prior computing composite score. Higher values composite score indicate better performance. ADNI study, components either collected partially certain study phase available . Since FSCRT available , Delayed Recall portion Alzheimer’s Disease Assessment Scale (ADAS), called ADAS-Cog Q4 score, used proxy. ADAS-Cog Q4 score ranges 0 10 points higher value indicates worse condition. Similarly, logarithm scale Trails B score used proxy DSST. Therefore, two modified version PACC composite score: mPACCdigit:  computed ADNI1 study phase since DSST collected early phase ADNI study. mPACCtrailsB:  computed across ADNI study phases using Trails B score proxy DSST.

title: ADNIMERGE2-PACC-SCORE
code: library(tidyverse) library(assertr) library(DT) library(labelled) # ADNI study R data package library(ADNIMERGE2)

title: ADNIMERGE2-PACC-SCORE
text: First, import pre-processed raw datasets contain PACC component ADNIMERGE2 package. raw datasets stored csv format external data package. reasons sourcing dataset 1) PACC component score yet available data-sharing platform, particularly ADAS-Cog Q4 score, 2) reduced potential additional package dependency. next r chunk, raw datasets loaded current working environment using load_csv_files() function. raw datasets long format presented follow: pacc_mmse_long: dataset contains MMSE score downloaded data-sharing platform. pacc_neurobat: dataset contains Logical Memory - Delayed Recall (LDELTOTL), Digit Symbol Substitution (DIGITSCR), Trials B (TRABSCOR) raw scores Neuropsychological Battery (NEUROBAT) data. NEUROBAT() data also downloaded data-sharing platform. pacc_adas_q4score_long: dataset contains raw ADAS-Cog Q4 score obtained two sources: Current study phase EDC portal Old version ADNI study R data package ADNIMERGE, also available data-sharing platform, contain records ADNI1 ADNI3 study phases.
code: # Import PACC input raw datasets pacc_raw_data_dir <- system.file(   "extradata/pacc-raw-input",   package = "ADNIMERGE2",   mustWork = TRUE ) load_csv_files(input_dir = pacc_raw_data_dir)

title: ADNIMERGE2-PACC-SCORE
text: raw dataset preparation, screening fail visit code ADNI1 study phase remapped actual screening visit code. Since PACC component assessments either collected baseline visit whole study partially collected baseline visit certain study phase. reasonable carrying forward screening visit record assessment corresponding baseline record baseline assessment result missing/unknown. instance, MMSE collected baseline visit, neuropsychological assessments (.e., LDELTOTL, DIGITSCR, TRABSCOR) partially collected baseline visit certain study phase. following r chuck demonstrate screening-baseline visit adjustment preformed carrying forward screening visit record baseline record using adjust_scbl_record() function. next step combine raw datasets converting combined data wide format using study data collection phase/protocol study visit code per subject. PACC component might collected date although assessments collected study visit. Additionally, component specific screening records carried forward baseline record including screening visit/assessment collection date. order representative common date associated PACC score per study visit, compare specific study visit date corresponding component collection date. use get_vars_common_date() function get common date per specific study visit per subject shown following two r chunks. maximum date selected component specific dates different. maximum date selection used due fact screening records carried forward baseline record.
code: # Adjustment of screening-baseline record id_vars <- c("COLPROT", "RID", "VISCODE", "SCORE_SOURCE")  ## MMSE ---- pacc_mmse_long <- pacc_mmse_long %>%   bind_rows(     adjust_scbl_record(       .data = pacc_mmse_long,       adjust_date_col = "VISDATE",       check_col = "SCORE"     ) %>%       filter(VISCODE %in% get_baseline_vistcode())   ) %>%   assert_uniq(all_of(id_vars)) %>%   set_as_tibble()  ## NEUROBAT ---- neurobat_vars <- c("LDELTOTL", "DIGITSCR", "TRABSCOR")  adjusted_bl_neurobat <- adjust_scbl_record(   .data = pacc_neurobat_long,   wide_format = FALSE,   extra_id_cols = "SCORE_SOURCE",   adjust_date_col = "VISDATE",   check_col = "SCORE" ) %>%   # Only baseline records   filter(VISCODE %in% get_baseline_vistcode())  pacc_neurobat_long <- pacc_neurobat_long %>%   filter(!VISCODE %in% get_baseline_vistcode()) %>%   bind_rows(adjusted_bl_neurobat) %>%   distinct() %>%   assert_uniq(all_of(id_vars)) %>%   set_as_tibble()  # ADAS-cog Q4 Score ---- pacc_adas_q4score_long <- pacc_adas_q4score_long %>%   set_as_tibble() # Bind PACC input raw-data pacc_input_data_long <- bind_rows(   pacc_mmse_long,   pacc_neurobat_long,   pacc_adas_q4score_long )  # Convert into wide format pacc_component <- c("ADASQ4SCORE", "MMSE", neurobat_vars)  pacc_input_data_wide <- pacc_input_data_long %>%   unite(col = "SCORE_VISDATE", SCORE, VISDATE, sep = "-/") %>%   pivot_wider(     names_from = SCORE_SOURCE,     values_from = SCORE_VISDATE   ) %>%   assert_uniq(all_of(c("COLPROT", "RID", "VISCODE"))) %>%   mutate(across(all_of(pacc_component), ~ strsplit(as.character(.), "-/"))) %>%   unnest_wider(all_of(pacc_component), names_sep = "_") %>%   rename_with(~ str_remove_all(.x, "\\_1$"), starts_with(pacc_component)) %>%   rename_with(~ str_replace_all(.x, "2$", "VISDATE"), starts_with(pacc_component)) %>%   mutate(across(starts_with(pacc_component), ~ ifelse(.x %in% "NA", NA, as.character(.x)))) %>%   mutate(across(all_of(pacc_component), as.numeric)) # Add visit date pacc_input_data_wide <- pacc_input_data_wide %>%   left_join(     REGISTRY %>%       select(COLPROT, RID, VISCODE, EXAMDATE) %>%       set_as_tibble(),     by = c("COLPROT", "RID", "VISCODE")   ) %>%   verify(nrow(.) == nrow(pacc_input_data_wide)) # Get common date per record pacc_input_data_wide <- get_vars_common_date(   .data = pacc_input_data_wide,   date_cols = paste0(pacc_component, "_VISDATE"),   compared_ref_date = TRUE,   ref_date_col = "EXAMDATE",   select_method = "max",   preferred_date_col = "COMMON_DATE" ) %>%   rename("PACC_VISDATE" = FINAL_DATE) pacc_input_data_wide <- pacc_input_data_wide %>%   # Add enrollment date   left_join(     get_adni_enrollment(.registry = REGISTRY) %>%       mutate(RID = as.character(RID)) %>%       select(ORIGPROT, RID, ENRLDT = EXAMDATE, ENRLFG),     by = "RID"   ) %>%   # Add baseline diagnostics status   left_join(     get_adni_blscreen_dxsum(       .dxsum = DXSUM,       phase = "Overall",       visit_type = "baseline"     ) %>%       mutate(RID = as.character(RID)) %>%       select(RID, DX = DIAGNOSIS, DXDATE = EXAMDATE) %>%       assert_uniq(RID),     by = "RID"   )

title: ADNIMERGE2-PACC-SCORE
text: next step calculate component specific baseline summaries used standardize component score. baseline summary based user-defined standardization population. , define standardization population follows: New enrolled subject ADNI study Subjects baseline Cognitive Normal (CN) diagnostics status following r chunk shows PACC component baseline score summarized across baseline diagnostics status based standardization population defined . summary result generated using compute_score_summary() function. NOTE:  recommended apply logarithm transformation Trials B score score already logarithm scale.
code: pacc_component_bl <- pacc_input_data_wide %>%   mutate(TRABSCOR = log(TRABSCOR + 1)) %>%   # Baseline visit for new enrollee   filter(ENRLFG %in% "Yes") %>%   group_by(RID) %>%   filter(ORIGPROT == COLPROT) %>%   filter(VISCODE %in% get_baseline_vistcode()) %>%   ungroup() %>%   assert_uniq(RID)  pacc_component_bl.summary <- compute_score_summary(   .data = pacc_component_bl,   wideFormat = TRUE,   scoreVar = pacc_component,   groupVar = "DX",   filterGroup = "CN" )  pacc_component_bl.summary %>%   mutate(VAR = ifelse(VAR == "TRABSCOR", "LOG.TRABSCOR", VAR)) %>%   # rename("Baseline DX" = DX, "Component" = VAR) %>%   datatable(     colnames = c("Baseline DX" = 2, "Component" = 3),     caption = "PACC Compoonent Standardization Baseline Summary"   )

title: ADNIMERGE2-PACC-SCORE
text: composite PACC score sum standardized component score adjusted number components. following two conditions checked computing PACC score. Trials B Measurement Scale: identify whether score logarithm scale. instance, Trials B score logarithm scale. need either map raw score values logarithm scale prior using scoring function specify argument allows perform logarithm transformation inside scoring function. Standardized Component Directional Effect: verify directional effect across standardized component score, reoriented standardized component score since composite score sum standardized scores. ADNI study, ADAS-cog Q4 Trials B scores opposite directional effect compared remaining PACC component scores. Higher values two components indicates worse condition. required convert direction effect two standardized components. Therefore, higher values composite score indicates better performance. Moreover, composite score calculated least two non-missing component scores given study visit per subject. , use compute_pacc_score() function compute two modified composite PACC scores ADNI study. next r chunk shows calculate PACC composite score based wide format input component score, standardization baseline summary, logarithm transformation Trials B score inside function.
code: PACC <- compute_pacc_score(   .data = pacc_input_data_wide,   bl.summary = pacc_component_bl.summary,   componentVars = pacc_component,   rescale_trialsB = TRUE,   keepComponents = TRUE,   wideFormat = TRUE ) %>%   mutate(RID = as.numeric(RID)) %>%   rename_with(~ str_replace_all(.x, "\\.zscore", "Z"), ends_with(".zscore")) %>%   create_orig_protocol()  PACC <- PACC %>%   select(all_of(pacc_data_dic$FLDNAME)) %>%   labelled::set_variable_labels(     .labels = pacc_data_dic$LABEL,     .strict = TRUE   )

title: ADNIMERGE2-PACC-SCORE
text: following r chunks show get baseline PACC composite score based PACC dataset. Similar result can obtained using ADSL ADQS datasets. information use datasets, please refer ADNI-Enrollment ADNIMERGE2-Analysis-Data articles.
code: # Modified PACC using DSS score baseline_mPACCdigit <- PACC %>%   # Only in ADNI1 study phase   filter(COLPROT == adni_phase()[1]) %>%   filter(ORIGPROT == COLPROT) %>%   filter(VISCODE %in% get_baseline_vistcode()) %>%   # Enrolled subjects   filter(ENRLFG %in% "Yes") %>%   assert_uniq(RID) %>%   select(RID, ORIGPROT, mPACCdigit, DX)  # Modified PACC using Trials B score as a proxy for DSS baseline_mPACCtrailsB <- PACC %>%   filter(ORIGPROT == COLPROT) %>%   filter(VISCODE %in% get_baseline_vistcode()) %>%   # Enrolled subjects   filter(ENRLFG %in% "Yes") %>%   assert_uniq(RID) %>%   select(RID, ORIGPROT, mPACCtrailsB, DX) baseline_PACC <- baseline_mPACCtrailsB %>%   mutate(     SCORE = mPACCtrailsB,     SCORE_NAME = "mPACCtrailsB"   ) %>%   bind_rows(     baseline_mPACCdigit %>%       mutate(         SCORE = mPACCdigit,         SCORE_NAME = "mPACCdigit"       )   ) %>%    group_by(SCORE_NAME) %>%    mutate(SCORE_NAME = paste0(SCORE_NAME, " (n = ", sum(!is.na(SCORE)), ")")) %>%    ungroup()  baseline_PACC %>%   ggplot2::ggplot(aes(x = SCORE)) +   geom_histogram() +   facet_wrap(~SCORE_NAME, scales = "free_y") +   labs(x = "Baseline Modified PACC Score", y = "Count") +   theme_bw(base_size = 12)

text: Furthermore, -4 value majority ADNI study phases -1 value ADNI1 study phase considered missing value. Therefore, values converted missing character value NA package. NOTE:  ℹ variable contains "-4" value message following two r chunks implies variables specified values ADNIMERGE2::DXSUM dataset since values already converted missing value prior package build .
code: # Convert "-4" into missing value convert_to_missing_value(   .data = ADNIMERGE2::DXSUM,   col_name = colnames(ADNIMERGE2::DXSUM),   value = "-4",   missing_char = NA,   phase = adni_phase() ) %>%   select(-PTID) %>%   head(.,0) #> ℹ No variable contains "-4" value #> # A tibble: 0 × 41 #> # ℹ 41 variables: ORIGPROT <chr>, COLPROT <fct>, RID <dbl>, VISCODE <chr>, #> #   VISCODE2 <chr>, EXAMDATE <date>, DIAGNOSIS <chr>, DXNORM <chr>, #> #   DXNODEP <chr>, DXMCI <chr>, DXMDES <chr>, DXMPTR1 <chr>, DXMPTR2 <chr>, #> #   DXMPTR3 <chr>, DXMPTR4 <chr>, DXMPTR5 <chr>, DXMPTR6 <chr>, DXMDUE <chr>, #> #   DXMOTHET <chr>, DXDSEV <chr>, DXDDUE <chr>, DXAD <chr>, DXAPP <chr>, #> #   DXAPROB <chr>, DXAPOSS <chr>, DXPARK <chr>, DXPDES <chr>, DXPCOG <chr>, #> #   DXPATYP <chr>, DXDEP <chr>, DXOTHDEM <chr>, DXODES <chr>, DXCONFID <chr>, … # Convert "-1" into missing value in ADNI1 phase only convert_to_missing_value(   .data = ADNIMERGE2::DXSUM,   col_name = NULL,   value = "-1",   missing_char = NA,   phase = "ADNI1" ) %>%   select(-PTID) %>%   head(.,0) #> ℹ No variable contains "-1" value #> # A tibble: 0 × 41 #> # ℹ 41 variables: ORIGPROT <chr>, COLPROT <fct>, RID <dbl>, VISCODE <chr>, #> #   VISCODE2 <chr>, EXAMDATE <date>, DIAGNOSIS <chr>, DXNORM <chr>, #> #   DXNODEP <chr>, DXMCI <chr>, DXMDES <chr>, DXMPTR1 <chr>, DXMPTR2 <chr>, #> #   DXMPTR3 <chr>, DXMPTR4 <chr>, DXMPTR5 <chr>, DXMPTR6 <chr>, DXMDUE <chr>, #> #   DXMOTHET <chr>, DXDSEV <chr>, DXDDUE <chr>, DXAD <chr>, DXAPP <chr>, #> #   DXAPROB <chr>, DXAPOSS <chr>, DXPARK <chr>, DXPDES <chr>, DXPCOG <chr>, #> #   DXPATYP <chr>, DXDEP <chr>, DXOTHDEM <chr>, DXODES <chr>, DXCONFID <chr>, …

title: ADNIMERGE2
text: part study data R package development, derived datasets created using PHARMAVERSE workflow illustration purpose. Detailed procedures datasets generated can found following package vignettes: ADNIMERGE2-Derived-Data: Includes standardized derived datasets ADNIMERGE2-Analysis-Meta-Specs: Includes metadata specification used generating derived analysis ready datasets. ADNIMERGE2-Analysis-Data: Includes derived analysis ready datasets based metadata specifications derived datasets. NOTE: recommended learn data generated see corresponding raw data source using derived data analysis. derived datasets package may fully complied CDISC standardization, data generated illustration purpose. Furthermore, derived data modified version Preclinical Alzheimer Cognitive Composite (PACC) score also included. ADNIMERGE2-PACC shows creating PACC score raw datasets.

title: ADNIMERGE2
text: articles included package vignette demonstrate use study data R package creating simple summaries analysis results. Enrollment Summaries: Includes enrollment summary calender month, enrolled subject demographic/characteristics summary study phases baseline diagnostics status (Cognitive Normal (CN), Mild Cognitive Impairment (MCI) Dementia (DEM)). Longitudinal Clinical Cognitive Outcome Summaries: Currently, includes summary ADAS Cognitive Behavior assessment item-13 total score (ADAS-cog) overtime across baseline diagnostics status. NOTE:  analysis results presented package vignettes pre-planned included illustration purpose.

1=Yes ; 0=Decoded Value: Yes PQRECON character Check following reconstruction algorithms used ADNIGO: 2=FORE/2D-OSEM (Siemens) ; 4=OSEM3D (Siemens) ; 5=3D Iterative (GE) ; 1=3D-Ramla (Philips) ; 3=3D Back-projection (GE) ADNI2: 2=FORE/2D-OSEM (Siemens) ; 4=OSEM3D (Siemens) ; 5=3D Iterative (GE) ; 6=FORE Iterative (GE) ; 1=3D LOR Ramla (Philips) ; 3=3D Back-projection (GE) Decoded Value: Yes PQCORNUM character FORE/2D-OSEM OSEM3D 3D Iterative FORE Iterative, correct # subsets iterations? 1=Yes ; 0=Decoded Value: Yes PQCORFIL character Correct Filters/TRIM? 1=Yes ; 0=Decoded Value: Yes PQCORTHI character Correct Slice Thickness (PET/CT systems)? 1=Yes ; 0=; 2=N/(PET system) Decoded Value: Yes PQVOXEL character Acceptable Voxel Size? 1=Yes ; 0=Decoded Value: Yes PQALLFRAME character frames acceptable? 1=Yes ; 0=Decoded Value: Yes PQUNUSABLE character Indicate frames unacceptable: PQREASON character Indicate frames unacceptable: 1=Subject motion ; 2=(Please Specify) Decoded Value: Yes PQREASSP character , Specify: PASS character Pass QC? 1=Yes ; 0=Decoded Value: Yes PQPROERR character . Processing Error(s) 1=Incorrect reconstruction algorithm ; 2=Incorrect filtering ; 3=Incorrect slice thickness ; 4=Incorrect voxel size ; 5=Attenuation Error ; 6=Normalization Error ; 7=Inadequate counts ; 8=Inadequate field view ; 9=Incorrect acquisition protocol ; 10=Unfixable image artifact (e.g. attenuation, normalization, etc.) ; 99=(specify) Decoded Value: Yes PQERRSP character Specify PQACTION character B. QC outcome 1=Request Reprocessing ; 2=Request Rescan ; 3=Unuseable - request rescan (provide details) ; 4=Allow Rescan (rescan requested) Decoded Value: Yes PQNONESP character unusable, reason rescanning PQISSUES character Imaging issues 1=Motion - minimal ; 2=Motion - mild ; 3=Motion - mild--moderate ; 4=Motion - moderate ; 5=Motion - moderate--severe ; 6=Top Cutoff - none ; 7=Top Cutoff - 0-3mm ; 8=Top Cutoff - 3-6mm ; 9=Top Cutoff - 6-9mm ; 10=Top Cutoff - >9mm ; 11=Bottom Cutoff - none ; 12=Bottom Cutoff - 0-3mm ; 13=Bottom Cutoff - 3-6mm ; 14=Bottom Cutoff - 6-9mm ; 15=Bottom Cutoff - >9mm ; 99=(specify) Decoded Value: Yes PQISSOTH character , specify , options: Good Images 3DRP COMMENTS character Additional QC Comments QUARANTINE character Release quarantine? 1=Yes ; 0=Decoded Value: Yes PAYSITE character Pay Site? 1=Yes ; 0=Decoded Value: Yes update_stamp     POSIXct: YYY-MM-DD

title: ADNI-1 3T Cross-Sectional FreeSurfer (5.1): 2016-02-01 — UCSFFSX51_ADNI1_3T
text: ORIGPROT character Original study protocol , options: ADNI1 RID numeric Participant roster ID Range value: 15, ..., 1387 VISCODE character Visit code , options: m36, m06, m24, m12, bl, m18 EXAMDATE   scan date image processed Date: YYY-MM-DD VERSION     Date: YYY-MM-DD LONISID numeric LONI study UID image processed Range value: 2613, ..., 24916 LONIUID numeric LONI series UID image processed. Range value: 8833, ..., 79768 IMAGEUID numeric ImageUID image processed. Range value: 32755, ..., 205567 RUNDATE     Date: YYY-MM-DD STATUS character   complete/partial OVERALLQC character overall quality rating. Refer additional QC variables Partial rating. Pass/Fail/Partial TEMPQC character QC rating temporal lobe. Fail affects following regions: LeftTemporalPole (ST60); RightTemporalPole (ST119); LeftFusiform (ST26); RightFusiform (ST85); LeftSuperiorTemporal (ST58); RightSuperiorTemporal (ST117); LeftInferiorTemporal (ST32); RightInferiorTemporal (ST91); LeftMiddleTemporal (ST40); RightMiddleTemporal (ST99) Pass/Fail FRONTQC character QC rating frontal lobe. Fail affects following regions: LeftFrontalPole (ST25); RightFrontalPole (ST84); LeftPrecentral (ST51); RightPrecentral (ST110); LeftSuperiorFrontal (ST56); RightSuperiorFrontal (ST115); LeftCaudalMiddleFrontal (ST15); RightCaudalMiddleFrontal (ST74); LeftRostralMiddleFrontal (ST55); RightRostralMiddleFrontal (ST114); LeftMedialOrbitofrontal (ST39); RightMedialOrbitofrontal (ST98) Pass/Fail PARQC character QC rating parietal lobe. Fail affects following regions: LeftPostcentral (ST49); RightPostcentral (ST108); LeftSuperiorParietal (ST57); RightSuperiorParietal (ST116); LeftSupraMarginal (ST59); RightSupraMarginal (ST118); LeftParacentral (ST43); RightParacentral (ST102); LeftInferiorParietal (ST31); RightInferiorParietal (ST90) Pass/Fail INSULAQC character QC rating insula. code: if (FALSE) { # \dontrun{ pacc_mmse_long_file <- system.file(   "/extradata/pacc-raw-input/pacc_mmse_long.csv",   package = "ADNIMERGE2" ) pacc_mmse_long <- readr::read_csv(   file = pacc_mmse_long_file,   guess_max = Inf ) # For a wide format data bl_sc_mmse_record <- adjust_scbl_record(   .data = pacc_mmse_long %>%     pivot_wider(names_from = SCORE_SOURCE, values_from = SCORE),   wide_format = TRUE ) head(bl_sc_mmse_record)  # For a long format data without adjusting for visit date bl_sc_mmse_record_long <- adjust_scbl_record(   .data = pacc_mmse_long,   wide_format = FALSE,   extra_id_cols = "SCORE_SOURCE" ) head(bl_sc_mmse_record_long)  # For a long format data with adjusting for visit date bl_sc_mmse_record_long <- adjust_scbl_record(   .data = pacc_mmse_long,   wide_format = FALSE,   extra_id_cols = "SCORE_SOURCE",   adjust_date_col = "VISDATE",   check_col = "SCORE" ) } # }

Please see arguments. bl.summary Baseline component score summary  can created either using compute_score_summary() function.  data.frame component score summary contains following variables: VAR: Contains PACC component variable names MEAN: Mean score SD: Standard deviation value Often recommended use baseline component score summarized  baseline diagnostics status. componentVars Character vector component score variable names. component score variable names arranged based following order. Otherwise, invalid composite score calculated. Delayed Recall portion ADAS Cognitive Behavior assessment (ADAS-Cog), see ADAS() Mini-Mental State Examination Score, see MMSE() Logical Memory IIa Delayed Recall Score, see LDELTOTAL score NEUROBAT() Digit Symbol Substitution Test Score, see DIGITSCOR score NEUROBAT() Trails B Score, see see TRABSCOR score NEUROBAT() rescale_trialsB Boolean value change Trails B score log scale, Default: TRUE keepComponents Boolean keep component score, Default: FALSE wideFormat Boolean value whether data.frame wide long format, Default: TRUE varName Column name contain component score names long format data, Default = NULL. applicable long format data varName must missing wideFormat FALSE. scoreCol Variable names contains component score/numeric value long format data, Default = NULL. applicable long format data scoreCol must missing wideFormat FALSE. idCols Character vector ID columns long format data, Default: NULL. applicable long format data idCols must missing wideFormat FALSE.

title: Compute ADNI modified versions of the Preclinical Alzheimer's Cognitive Composite (PACC) — compute_pacc_score
text: function generates two modified versions PACC scores based ADNI data. FCSRT used ADNI, use Delayed Recall portion Alzheimer's Disease Assessment Scale (ADAS) proxy. Score mPACCdigit uses DSST computed ADNI1 study phase. mPACCtrailsB uses (log transformed) Trails B proxy DSST. Raw component scores standardized according mean standard deviation baseline scores ADNI subjects normal cognition create Z scores component (Z=(raw - mean(raw.bl))/sd(raw.bl)). Z scores reoriented necessary greater scores reflect better performance. composite sum Z scores. Missing components: least two components must present produce score. two components missing, PACC NA. mPACCdigit calculated study phase DSST collected, ADNI1 study phase.  Otherwise mPACCdigit score missing (.e., NA) even though remaining PACC component scores non-missing. Please see vignette(topic = "ADNIMERGE2-PACC-SCORE", package = "ADNIMERGE2") compute_pacc_score() function can used.

title: Compute ADNI modified versions of the Preclinical Alzheimer's Cognitive Composite (PACC) — compute_pacc_score
text: Donohue MC, et al. Preclinical Alzheimer Cognitive Composite: Measuring Amyloid-Related Decline. JAMA Neurol. 2014;71(8):961–970. doi:10.1001/jamaneurol.2014.803 http://dx.doi.org/10.1001/jamaneurol.2014.803 Donohue MC, Sperling RA, Petersen R, Sun C, Weiner MW, Aisen PS, Alzheimer’s Disease Neuroimaging Initiative. Association Elevated Brain Amyloid Subsequent Cognitive Decline Among Cognitively Normal Persons. JAMA. 2017;317(22):2305–2316. http://dx.doi.org/10.1001/jama.2017.6669

title: Compute ADNI modified versions of the Preclinical Alzheimer's Cognitive Composite (PACC) — compute_pacc_score
Compute ADNI modified versions of the Preclinical Alzheimer's Cognitive Composite (PACC) — compute_pacc_score
code: if (FALSE) { # \dontrun{ # Please see 'Details' section or 'ADNIMERGE2-PACC-SCORE' vignette vignette(topic = "ADNIMERGE2-PACC-SCORE", package = "ADNIMERGE2")  # Additional examples about PACC score ----- library(nlme) library(dplyr) library(multcomp) library(Hmisc) library(ADNIMERGE)  csf2numeric <- function(x) {   as.numeric(gsub("<", "", gsub(">", "", x))) }  dd <- subset(adnimerge, DX.bl %in% c("CN", "SMC") & !is.na(mPACCtrailsB)) %>%   mutate(     ABETA = csf2numeric(ABETA)   )  # identify those with elevated PIB PET at ANY visit OR # elevated BASELINE AV45 PET OR elevated BASELINE FBB PET OR # low BASELINE CSF Abeta # AV45 ~ PIB regression from Landau et al 2012: elevatedAmyloid <- unique(c(   subset(dd, 0.67 * PIB + 0.15 > 1.11)$RID,   subset(dd, VISCODE == "bl" & AV45 > 1.11)$RID,   subset(dd, VISCODE == "bl" & FBB > 1.08)$RID,   subset(dd, VISCODE == "bl" & ABETA < 900)$RID )) anyAmyloid <- unique(subset(dd, !is.na(AV45.bl) | !is.na(PIB) |   !is.na(FBB.bl) | !is.na(ABETA.bl))$RID)  dd <- dd %>%   mutate(     ElevatedAmyloid = ifelse(RID %in% elevatedAmyloid, 1,       ifelse(RID %in% anyAmyloid, 0, NA)     ),     m = Month.bl,     m2 = Month.bl^2,     APOEe4 = APOE4 > 0   )  summary(   ElevatedAmyloid ~ APOEe4 + AGE + PTEDUCAT,   data = dd,   subset = VISCODE == "bl",   method = "reverse",   overall = TRUE )  # Quadratic time model: fit <- lme(   fixed = mPACCtrailsB ~ mPACCtrailsB.bl + APOEe4 + AGE +     PTEDUCAT + m + m2 + (m + m2):ElevatedAmyloid,   random = ~ m | RID,   data = dd,   na.action = na.omit )  Months <- seq(12, 96, 12) elevated.design <- model.matrix(   mPACCtrailsB ~ mPACCtrailsB.bl + APOEe4 + AGE + PTEDUCAT +     m + m2 + (m + m2):ElevatedAmyloid,   data = data.frame(     mPACCtrailsB = 0, mPACCtrailsB.bl = 0, APOEe4 = TRUE, AGE = 75,     PTEDUCAT = 12, ElevatedAmyloid = 1, m = Months, m2 = Months^2   ) )  normal.design <- model.matrix(   mPACCtrailsB ~ mPACCtrailsB.bl + APOEe4 + AGE + PTEDUCAT +     m + m2 + (m + m2):ElevatedAmyloid,   data = data.frame(     mPACCtrailsB = 0, mPACCtrailsB.bl = 0, APOEe4 = TRUE, AGE = 75,     PTEDUCAT = 12, ElevatedAmyloid = 0, m = Months, m2 = Months^2   ) )  contrast.data <- elevated.design - normal.design summary(multcomp::glht(fit, linfct = contrast.data)) } # }

code: if (FALSE) { # \dontrun{ library(tidyverse) library(ADNIMERGE2)  # Enrollment flag enrollment_flag <- ADNIMERGE2::REGISTRY %>%   get_adni_enrollment(.registry = .) %>%   mutate(ENRLDT = as.Date(EXAMDATE)) %>%   select(RID, ENRLDT)  # Baseline diagnostics status for newly enrolled subject in ADNI study overall_baseline_dx <- get_adni_blscreen_dxsum(   .dxsum = ADNIMERGE2::DXSUM,   phase = "Overall",   visit_type = "baseline" ) %>%   left_join(     enrollment_flag,     by = "RID"   ) %>%   # Only enrolled subjects   filter(ENRLFG %in% "Yes")  # Phase-specific baseline diagnostic status: ----- # When subject enrolled in ADNI3 study phase adni3_baseline_dx <- get_adni_blscreen_dxsum(   .dxsum = ADNIMERGE2::DXSUM,   phase = "ADNI3",   visit_type = "baseline" ) %>%   left_join(     enrollment_flag,     by = "RID"   ) %>%   # Only enrolled subjects   filter(ENRLFG %in% "Yes")  # Screening Diagnostics Status: ----- # When subject were screened for first time in ADNI study. first_screen_dx <- get_adni_blscreen_dxsum(   .dxsum = ADNIMERGE2::DXSUM,   phase = "Overall",   visit_type = "screen" ) # Phase-specific screening diagnostic status: ------ # When subject were screened for ADNI4 study phase adni3_screen_dx <- get_adni_blscreen_dxsum(   .dxsum = ADNIMERGE2::DXSUM,   phase = "ADNI4",   visit_type = "screen" ) } # }

text: x Numeric value baseline_summary data.frame baseline score summary contains following variables: MEAN: Mean value SD: Standard deviation value VAR: Contains variable name. applicable non-missing varName value. baseline_summary can generated using compute_baseline_score_summary() function. varName Variable name

title: Standardize/normalize numeric value by baseline summary — normalize_var_by_baseline_score
Standardize/normalize numeric value by baseline summary — normalize_var_by_baseline_score
code: if (FALSE) { # \dontrun{ # Suppose we wanted to standardize/normalize ADASTT13 scores in # ADNIMERGE2:ADQS by baseline summary score of Cognitive Normal (CN) # enrolled subjects.  library(tidyverse) library(assertr) library(ADNIMERGE2)  bl.summary <- ADNIMERGE2::ADSL %>%   compute_baseline_score_summary(     .data = ADNIMERGE2::ADSL,     filterBy = "ENRLFL",     filterValue = "Y",     wideFormat = TRUE,     scoreVar = "ADASTT13",     groupVar = "DX",     filterGroup = "CN"   )  # Using numeric vector example_data1 <- ADNIMERGE2::ADQS %>%   filter(PARAMCD %in% "ADASTT13") rsample_adas13 <- example_data1$AVAL rsample_adas13 <- sample(rsample_adas13, size = 100) normalize_var_by_baseline_score(   x = rsample_adas13,   baseline_summary = bl.summary,   varName = NULL )  # Using data.frame format  example_data2 <- ADNIMERGE2::ADQS %>%   mutate(across(AVAL,     ~ normalize_var_by_baseline_score(       x = .x,       baseline_summary = bl.summary,       varName = "ADASTT13"     ),     .names = "{col}.zscore"   ))  example_data2 %>%   group_by(PARAMCD, !is.na(AVAL), !is.na(AVAL.zscore)) %>%   count() %>%   ungroup()  library(ggplot2)  example_data2 %>%   filter(PARAMCD %in% "ADASTT13") %>%   pivot_longer(     cols = c("AVAL", "AVAL.zscore"),     names_to = "SOURCE",     values_to = "VALUE"   ) %>%   ggplot(aes(x = VALUE)) +   geom_histogram() +   facet_wrap(~SOURCE) } # }
